                     <title key="work_7321"><supplied>Sermo in festo sancti Andreae</supplied></title>
                     <note>(cc. 3–12)</note>
                     <rubric>Tractatus beati Bernardi abbatis de confessione</rubric>
                     <incipit>Corde creditur ad iusticiam, ore autem confessio fit ad salutem. Dicit enim scriptura Omnis qui credit in illum non confundet. Tria proponuntur hec, et corde credere ad iusticiam, et ore confiteri, et in illum credere </incipit>
                     <explicit>finem loquendi pariter audiamus. Det nobis deus corde credere ad iusticiam</explicit>
                     <note><bibl>J. Leclercq, ‘Les Collections de Sermons de Nicolas de Clairvaux’, repr. in <title>Recueil d'études sur saint Bernard et ses écrits</title>, I.53 (no. 14); PL 184.1050–1056; also PL 144.830–4 (as Peter Damian), Schneyer V.477 (as Stephen Langton 146).</bibl></note>
